    56	## WF-1: Define assistant and start runtime
    57	
    58	**Package:** `core`
    59	**Depends on:** `docs/specs/v1-core-spec.md` (after Contradiction 1ŌĆō3 resolutions applied)
    60	**Produces:** `AssistantDefinition`, `AssistantRuntime`, `createAssistant`, lifecycle state machine, `runtime.status()`
    61	**PR scope:** `packages/core/src/types.ts`, `packages/core/src/core.ts`, `packages/core/src/core.test.ts`
    62	
    63	### Steps
    64	
    65	1. Define an `AssistantDefinition` with `id`, `name`, and a `capabilities` map (`Record<string, CapabilityHandler>`)
    66	2. Call `createAssistant(definition, { inbound: stubAdapter, outbound: stubAdapter })` ŌĆö returns `AssistantRuntime`
    67	3. Call `runtime.start()` ŌĆö verify `runtime.status().ready === true`
    68	4. Call `runtime.stop()` ŌĆö verify runtime is no longer accepting dispatches
    69	5. Verify double-start is idempotent or throws expected error
    70	6. Verify double-stop is idempotent or throws expected error
    71	
    72	### Acceptance criteria
