    89	## WF-2: Handle inbound message via capability dispatch
    90	
    91	**Package:** `core`
    92	**Depends on:** WF-1
    93	**Produces:** capability dispatch table, `runtime.dispatch()`, `AssistantHooks.onMessage` pre-filter, `runtime.emit()`, `InboundMessage` / `OutboundEvent` types
    94	**PR scope:** additions to `packages/core/src/types.ts`, additions to `packages/core/src/core.ts`, new test cases in `packages/core/src/core.test.ts`
    95	
    96	### Steps
    97	
    98	1. Create and start a runtime with a capability named `"chat"` mapped to a handler function
    99	2. Call `runtime.dispatch(inboundMessage)` where `inboundMessage.capability === "chat"`
   100	3. Verify the `"chat"` handler is called with the correct `InboundMessage` and `CapabilityContext`
   101	4. Handler calls `context.runtime.emit(outboundEvent)` ŌĆö verify stub outbound adapter receives the event
   102	5. Register an `onMessage` hook that returns `false` ŌĆö verify dispatch is dropped before handler is called
   103	6. Dispatch a message with an unregistered capability ŌĆö verify expected error or no-op behavior
   104	7. Verify `runtime.status().inFlightHandlers` tracks concurrent handler invocations
   105	
