   163	## WF-4: Wire session store into runtime
   164	
   165	**Package:** `core` + `sessions`
   166	**Depends on:** WF-2, WF-3
   167	**Produces:** `runtime.register('sessions', store)`, session resolution in capability handler context, `resolveSession()` utility integration
   168	**PR scope:** additions to `packages/core/src/core.ts` (register/get validation), new integration test `packages/core/src/core-sessions.test.ts`
   169	
   170	> **Cross-package note:** Sessions does not inject session middleware into core's dispatch pipeline. Products wire session lookups into capability handlers themselves using `context.runtime.get<SessionStore>('sessions')` and the `resolveSession()` utility exported by `@relay-assistant/sessions`. Core remains unaware of session semantics.
   171	
   172	### Steps
   173	
   174	1. Create an `AssistantRuntime` and a `SessionStore`
   175	2. Call `runtime.register('sessions', store)` ŌĆö verify `runtime.status().registeredSubsystems` includes `'sessions'`
   176	3. In the capability handler, call `context.runtime.get<SessionStore>('sessions')` ŌĆö verify it returns the store
   177	4. Use `resolveSession(message, store, defaultAffinityResolver)` inside the handler ŌĆö verify it creates a new session for a new userId (reads `message.userId`)
   178	5. Dispatch a second message with the same userId ŌĆö verify `resolveSession` returns the existing session
   179	6. Touch the session inside the handler ŌĆö verify `session.state === 'active'`
   180	7. Verify `runtime.get('nonexistent')` throws with a clear error
   181	
   182	### Acceptance criteria
   183	
   184	- `runtime.register(name, subsystem)` returns `AssistantRuntime` for chaining
   185	- `runtime.get<T>(name)` is generic; throws if name is not registered
   186	- `resolveSession()` utility is exported from `packages/sessions/src/index.ts`
   187	- `resolveSession` reads `message.userId` (required field per Contradiction 2 resolution) for session lookup ŌĆö no manual userId extraction from `message.raw`
   188	- Integration test does not import any surfaces package
   189	- Session auto-create and session reuse are both tested
