   241	## WF-6: Multi-surface session fanout
   242	
   243	**Package:** `core` + `sessions` + `surfaces`
   244	**Depends on:** WF-4, WF-5
   245	**Produces:** cross-surface session attachment, `surfaceRegistry.fanout()`, targeted-vs-fanout outbound rule validated in integration
   246	**PR scope:** new integration test `packages/core/src/core-sessions-surfaces.test.ts`
   247	
   248	> **Fanout ownership note:** The surfaces package owns fanout delivery. When `runtime.emit()` is called without a `surfaceId`, core resolves the session's `attachedSurfaces` and calls `surfaceRegistry.fanout(event, attachedSurfaceIds, policy?)`. The registry handles concurrent delivery and collects `FanoutResult`. Sessions owns the `attachedSurfaces` list; surfaces owns delivery.
   249	
   250	### Steps
   251	
   252	1. Create a runtime with sessions and a surface registry (slack + web connections)
   253	2. User sends a message via slack surface ŌĆö `resolveSession()` creates a new session; `store.attachSurface(sessionId, 'slack-1')` is called
   254	3. Same userId sends a message via web surface ŌĆö `resolveSession()` returns existing session; `store.attachSurface(sessionId, 'web-1')` is called
   255	4. Verify `session.attachedSurfaces` contains both `'slack-1'` and `'web-1'`
   256	5. Handler emits `OutboundEvent` with `surfaceId` set to originating surface ŌĆö verify only that surface's adapter receives the event (targeted send via `surfaceRegistry.send()`)
   257	6. Handler emits `OutboundEvent` with `sessionId` but no `surfaceId` ŌĆö verify `surfaceRegistry.fanout()` is called and both adapters receive the event (session fanout)
   258	7. Handler emits `OutboundEvent` with neither `surfaceId` nor `sessionId` ŌĆö verify `runtime.emit()` throws `OutboundEventError`
   259	8. Call `store.detachSurface(sessionId, 'slack-1')` ŌĆö verify fanout no longer includes slack
   260	9. Verify `FanoutResult` reports correct `total`, `delivered`, `outcomes` fields
   261	
   262	### Acceptance criteria
   263	
   264	- Session correctly accumulates surface references across multiple surface interactions from the same userId
   265	- Targeted send (`surfaceId` present) routes only to the specified adapter via `surfaceRegistry.send()`
   266	- Fanout (`sessionId` present, no `surfaceId`) routes to all `session.attachedSurfaces` via `surfaceRegistry.fanout()`
   267	- Invalid emit (neither `surfaceId` nor `sessionId`) throws `OutboundEventError` (per Contradiction 3 resolution)
   268	- Detach behavior removes surface from fanout targets
   269	- No session duplication for same userId across surfaces
   270	- `FanoutResult` structure is correct per spec
   271	
