   115	
   116	### Sage Adoption Path
   117	
   118	**Weekend goal:** Wire core + sessions + surfaces. Draft a memory adapter interface stub so v1.1 memory integration can start Monday.
   119	
   120	| Step | Action |
   121	| --- | --- |
   122	| v1 | Install core, sessions, surfaces. Define the Sage assistant identity using `createAssistant()`. Wire `createSessionStore({ adapter: new InMemorySessionStoreAdapter() })`. Register a Slack `SurfaceConnection` in a `SurfaceRegistry`. |
   123	| Immediate after v1 | Begin adapter stub for `@relay-assistant/memory` (v1.1). Sage's existing memory patterns are the primary signal for the memory spec. |
   124	| v1.1 gates | Full memory persistence across Sage sessions. Proactive follow-up engine. |
   125	
   126	**Sage v1 minimum viable assembly:**
   127	
   128	```ts
   129	import { createAssistant } from "@relay-assistant/core";
   130	import type { AssistantDefinition, InboundMessage, CapabilityContext } from "@relay-assistant/core";
   131	import { createSessionStore, InMemorySessionStoreAdapter, resolveSession, createDefaultAffinityResolver } from "@relay-assistant/sessions";
   132	import type { SessionStore } from "@relay-assistant/sessions";
   133	import { createSurfaceRegistry } from "@relay-assistant/surfaces";
   134	import type { SurfaceConnection, SurfaceCapabilities } from "@relay-assistant/surfaces";
   135	
   136	// 1. Define the Sage assistant
   137	const definition: AssistantDefinition = {
   138	  id: "sage",
   139	  name: "Sage",
   140	  capabilities: {
   141	    chat: async (message: InboundMessage, context: CapabilityContext) => {
   142	      // Resolve or create a session for this user
   143	      const store = context.runtime.get<SessionStore>("sessions");
   144	      const session = await resolveSession(
   145	        message,
   146	        store,
   147	        createDefaultAffinityResolver(store),
   148	      );
   149	      await store.touch(session.id);
   150	
   151	      // Sage domain handler ŌĆö product-owned logic
   152	      await context.runtime.emit({
   153	        surfaceId: message.surfaceId,
   154	        sessionId: session.id,
   155	        text: "...", // Sage-specific response
   156	      });
   157	    },
   158	  },
   159	};
   160	
   161	// 2. Wire sessions
   162	const sessionStore = createSessionStore({
   163	  adapter: new InMemorySessionStoreAdapter(),
   164	});
   165	
   166	// 3. Wire surfaces (relay foundation provides real SurfaceAdapter implementations)
   167	const slackCapabilities: SurfaceCapabilities = {
   168	  markdown: false,
   169	  richBlocks: true,
   170	  attachments: true,
   171	  streaming: false,
   172	  maxResponseLength: 3000,
   173	};
   174	
   175	const slackConnection: SurfaceConnection = {
   176	  id: "sage-slack",
   177	  type: "slack",
   178	  state: "registered",
   179	  capabilities: slackCapabilities,
   180	  adapter: stubSlackAdapter, // provided by relay foundation or product code
   181	  formatHook: (event, caps) => ({ blocks: [{ type: "section", text: event.text }] }),
   182	};
   183	
   184	const surfaceRegistry = createSurfaceRegistry();
   185	surfaceRegistry.register(slackConnection);
   186	
   187	// 4. Create runtime and register subsystems
   188	const runtime = createAssistant(definition, {
   189	  inbound: surfaceRegistry,
   190	  outbound: surfaceRegistry,
   191	});
   192	runtime.register("sessions", sessionStore);
   193	
   194	await runtime.start();
   195	```
   196	
   197	**What stays in Sage for now:**
   198	- Knowledge and workspace-specific prompt behavior
   199	- Product-specific follow-up heuristics
   200	- Slack-specific UI conventions and block kit templates
   201	- Memory retrieval logic (until v1.1 `@relay-assistant/memory` ships)
