   252	## 4. Package Boundaries
   253	
   254	### Depends on (external)
   255	- Standard TypeScript runtime; no framework dependencies.
   256	- Node.js `EventEmitter` (or equivalent) for internal event bus. No external event library.
   257	
   258	### Depends on (internal)
   259	- Nothing from this monorepo. Core is the dependency root.
   260	
   261	### Depended on by (internal)
   262	- All other `@relay-assistant/*` packages import types from core.
   263	
   264	### Relay foundation boundary
   265	- Core calls into the relay foundation through **adapters**, not directly. Two adapter interfaces are defined in core:
   266	
   267	```typescript
   268	/** Injected by the relay foundation to push inbound events into core. */
   269	export interface RelayInboundAdapter {
   270	  onMessage(handler: (raw: unknown) => void): void;
   271	  offMessage(handler: (raw: unknown) => void): void;
   272	}
   273	
   274	/** Injected by the relay foundation to deliver outbound events. */
   275	export interface RelayOutboundAdapter {
   276	  send(event: OutboundEvent): Promise<void>;
   277	}
   278	```
   279	
   280	The relay foundation implements these interfaces. Core never imports relay packages.
   281	
