   313	
   314	## 7. OSS vs Cloud Boundary
   315	
   316	All types and factory functions in this spec are OSS. Nothing in core requires a hosted service.
   317	
   318	The relay foundation layer (inbound/outbound adapters) may be implemented in OSS or cloud variants; core does not know which.
   319	
   320	Cloud-only behavior (e.g., managed relay connections, centralized health dashboards) is implemented in a separate package that wraps core, never by modifying core.
