   295	### 4.10 Normalization
   296	
   297	Inbound normalization extracts these fields from a raw relay event:
   298	
   299	| Target field | Source | Fallback |
   300	|---|---|---|
   301	| `id` | `raw.messageId` or `raw.id` | Generated UUID |
   302	| `surfaceId` | Provided by relay (first arg to `receiveRaw`) | Error if missing |
   303	| `sessionId` | `raw.sessionId` or `raw.session?.id` | undefined |
   304	| `text` | `raw.text` or `raw.content` or `raw.body` | Empty string; logs warning |
   305	| `receivedAt` | `raw.timestamp` or `raw.receivedAt` | `new Date().toISOString()` |
   306	| `raw` | Verbatim | Required |
   307	
   308	Normalization does not fail on missing optional fields; it logs warnings and uses fallbacks.
