   359	## 6. Package Boundaries
   360	
   361	### Depends on
   362	- `@relay-assistant/core` ŌĆö imports `InboundMessage`, `OutboundEvent` types. The `SurfaceRegistry` acts as the inbound relay adapter for core.
   363	- `@relay-assistant/sessions` ŌĆö imports `Session` type to read `attachedSurfaces` for fanout.
   364	
   365	### Depended on by
   366	- Product code that registers surface connections.
   367	- `@relay-assistant/proactive` ŌĆö calls `surfaceRegistry.send()` or `fanout()` to deliver proactive messages.
   368	
   369	### Relay foundation boundary
   370	- Surfaces never opens sockets or calls relay APIs directly. The relay foundation calls `surfaceRegistry.receiveRaw()` (push model) and implements `SurfaceAdapter.send()` for each surface type.
   371	- The separation is explicit: relay handles transport; surfaces handles normalization, format, and fanout.
